ðŸ§¾ GIT CHEAT-SHEET (BEGINNER FRIENDLY)
ðŸ”¹ Basic Navigation

Go to a folder
cd folder_name

Go back one folder
cd ..

Check current location
pwd

Create new folder
mkdir folder_name

ðŸ”¹ Repository Setup

Initialize git repository
git init

Check repository status
git status

ðŸ”¹ Staging & Committing

Add all changes
git add .

Add specific file
git add filename

Commit changes
git commit -m "commit message"

ðŸ”¹ Branch Commands

Check all branches
git branch

Create new branch
git branch newbranch

Switch to branch
git checkout newbranch

Create & switch (shortcut)
git checkout -b newbranch

Delete branch (after merge)
git branch -d newbranch

ðŸ”¹ Remote Repository (GitHub)

Add remote repository
git remote add origin <repo-link>

Verify remote
git remote -v

Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main

Pull latest changes
git pull origin main

ðŸ”¹ Working with Pull Requests (PR)

Push branch
git push -u origin newbranch

Open GitHub

Click Compare & Pull Request

Base â†’ main, Compare â†’ newbranch

Create PR â†’ Merge PR

ðŸ”¹ Merge Branch (Local)

Switch to main
git checkout main

Merge branch
git merge newbranch

ðŸ”¹ Merge Conflict (Important!)

If you see:

<<<<<<< HEAD
=======
>>>>>>> newbranch


Steps:

Open the file

Fix the code/content

Remove conflict markers

Save file

Run:

git add .
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflict"

ðŸ”¹ Daily Git Flow (Must Remember)
git status
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git push

